verses.verse: Unto you lift I up <S%H5375><s%> my eyes <S%H5869><s%>, O you that dwell <S%H3427><s%> in the heavens <S%H8064><s%>.

Behold <S%H5869><s%>, as the eyes of servants <S%H5650><s%> look unto the hand <S%H3027><s%> of their masters <S%H113><s%>, and as the eyes <S%H5869><s%> of a maiden <S%H8198><s%> unto the hand <S%H3027><s%> of her mistress <S%H1404><s%>; so our eyes <S%H5869><s%> wait upon the Lord <S%H3068><s%> our God <S%H430><s%>, until that he have mercy upon us <S%H2603><s%>.
Have mercy <S%H2603><s%> upon us <S%H3068><s%>, O Lord, have mercy <S%H2603><s%> upon us <S%H7227><s%>: for we are exceedingly filled <S%H7646><s%> with contempt <S%H937><s%>.

Our soul <S%H5315><s%> is exceedingly <S%H7227><s%> filled <S%H7646><s%> with the scorning <S%H3933><s%> of those that are at ease <S%H7600><s%>, and with the contempt <S%H937><s%> of the proud <S%H1343><s%>.
